    "spell": {
        "name": "Falsify Heat",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "text": "You veil the signs of the fires of vitality, altering the target's apparent body temperature. This illusion applies to all senses, and a creature that touches the target can attempt to disbelieve the illusion. You can Dismiss the spell. Choose an illusory body temperature when you cast the spell.\n* **Moderate** The target's body temperature appears the same as the surrounding environment, giving the target a +2 circumstance bonus to Deception checks to Impersonate an undead, a cold-blooded creature, or an inanimate object (such as a corpse). The target is also invisible to *heatvision* and other abilities that sense heat similarly.\n* **Warm** The target appears to emit substantial body heat, gaining a +2 circumstance bonus to Deception checks to Impersonate a warm-blooded creature.",
        "subtype": "spell",
        "spell_type": "spell",
        "rank": 2,
